1
00:00:13,736 --> 00:00:15,306
Her recovery is slow.

2
00:00:15,306 --> 00:00:17,846
I can't say for sure
how long she'll hold out.

3
00:00:17,847 --> 00:00:19,976
Hee Tae, you'll be a great doctor.

4
00:00:19,976 --> 00:00:21,576
I only accepted you as my son...

5
00:00:21,576 --> 00:00:23,882
because I believed
you would prove useful.

6
00:00:24,146 --> 00:00:26,182
Hee Tae!

7
00:00:26,317 --> 00:00:29,621
Please save Seok Chul! Please!

8
00:00:52,647 --> 00:00:54,612
Oh, you're up.

9
00:00:55,176 --> 00:00:56,981
You should have some hangover soup.

10
00:00:57,547 --> 00:00:58,712
Yes.

11
00:01:00,356 --> 00:01:01,682
Where's Myeong Hee?

12
00:01:29,717 --> 00:01:31,041
Myeong Hee.

13
00:01:32,717 --> 00:01:35,152
I'm ready to be hurt.

14
00:01:38,286 --> 00:01:42,291
Do you want to go out with me
just until the end of May?

15
00:01:52,607 --> 00:01:54,032
Let's talk later.

16
00:01:56,107 --> 00:01:57,972
I'll give you my answer...

17
00:01:58,506 --> 00:02:00,271
when you're sober.

18
00:02:07,217 --> 00:02:08,612
Ms. Kim.

19
00:02:09,657 --> 00:02:12,456
The manager said you can stop by
before lunch for the meeting.

20
00:02:12,456 --> 00:02:14,522
Okay, I will.

21
00:02:16,566 --> 00:02:19,631
By the way, do you have a fever?

22
00:02:19,696 --> 00:02:22,661
Your face looks a bit flushed.

23
00:02:26,237 --> 00:02:28,032
Maybe it's my spring tan.

24
00:02:34,177 --> 00:02:38,511
(Episode 4, Crossing the Line)

25
00:02:40,856 --> 00:02:43,182
My goodness.

26
00:02:48,027 --> 00:02:51,866
Okay. So everyone is available
next week, right?

27
00:02:51,867 --> 00:02:53,937
You made such a big fuss
first thing in the morning,

28
00:02:53,937 --> 00:02:55,932
so I thought
it was about something important.

29
00:02:56,036 --> 00:02:57,166
It is important.

30
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:59,036
Everyone in Seoul wants
Gwangju's confirmation...

31
00:02:59,036 --> 00:03:01,907
and vice versa.
You're all just putting it off.

32
00:03:01,907 --> 00:03:05,571
Anyway, I'll give this date
to those in Seoul.

33
00:03:05,777 --> 00:03:08,941
What is your relationship
with Jang Seok Chul, by the way?

34
00:03:09,946 --> 00:03:12,816
She's neither your family
nor your spouse.

35
00:03:12,816 --> 00:03:14,856
Why are you putting so much time,
money, and effort into this?

36
00:03:14,856 --> 00:03:18,022
I have to say, I'm really curious.

37
00:03:24,666 --> 00:03:26,832
I'd say, we're offender and victim.

38
00:03:27,937 --> 00:03:29,402
Let's leave it at that.

39
00:03:30,566 --> 00:03:33,036
1, 2, 1, 2. Halt!

40
00:03:33,036 --> 00:03:34,302
1, 2!

41
00:03:38,247 --> 00:03:39,541
What are you doing?

42
00:03:41,476 --> 00:03:43,611
I told you not to make it so obvious
that you're a leftist nerd.

43
00:03:44,087 --> 00:03:46,016
Private Kim Kyung Soo!

44
00:03:46,016 --> 00:03:49,212
I wasn't studying.

45
00:03:49,356 --> 00:03:50,522
Hand it over.

46
00:03:51,957 --> 00:03:53,122
About, face!

47
00:03:53,657 --> 00:03:55,296
You dimwit.

48
00:03:55,296 --> 00:03:58,291
Must you always be one step behind?
You drive me crazy.

49
00:03:59,766 --> 00:04:01,261
Here it is, sir.

50
00:04:06,207 --> 00:04:08,532
My gosh. A letter?

51
00:04:09,307 --> 00:04:10,945
Are you planning
a secret rendezvous...

52
00:04:10,946 --> 00:04:12,472
with your comrades outside?

53
00:04:17,587 --> 00:04:20,152
Even going forward,
you're not allowed...

54
00:04:20,356 --> 00:04:21,911
to send letters
or make any phone calls.

55
00:04:23,386 --> 00:04:26,251
- Answer me!
- Yes, sir!

56
00:04:33,667 --> 00:04:36,731
Yes, we'd like to transfer
patient Jang Seok Chul.

57
00:04:39,136 --> 00:04:41,902
Right, we made the decision
with the risks in mind.

58
00:04:43,047 --> 00:04:46,041
The hospital in Gwangju can do it
next week.

59
00:04:47,377 --> 00:04:48,741
Two weeks?

60
00:04:51,316 --> 00:04:53,116
Can we expedite it a little?

61
00:04:53,117 --> 00:04:54,911
As you know,
the patient's current condition...

62
00:04:54,917 --> 00:04:56,357
Aren't you going to have lunch?

63
00:04:56,357 --> 00:04:58,522
- You go ahead.
- Okay.

64
00:05:04,227 --> 00:05:06,092
Yes, I'm aware.

65
00:05:09,607 --> 00:05:11,132
Right, so...

66
00:05:12,506 --> 00:05:13,731
That's why...

67
00:05:19,917 --> 00:05:22,041
(Pay Phone)

68
00:05:25,117 --> 00:05:27,582
Yes. Please kindly look into it,
Professor.

69
00:05:34,526 --> 00:05:35,892
Myeong Hee.

70
00:05:37,867 --> 00:05:40,192
What brings you to the hospital?

71
00:05:41,297 --> 00:05:43,636
Oh, I have a bad hangover.

72
00:05:43,636 --> 00:05:46,472
I was hoping to get
some IV fluids in the ER.

73
00:05:47,037 --> 00:05:49,001
It doesn't look like
that's why you're here.

74
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:51,276
What is it? Did something happen?

75
00:05:51,276 --> 00:05:53,642
No, it's nothing.

76
00:05:54,646 --> 00:05:57,416
I have to say, you're so mean.

77
00:05:57,417 --> 00:05:59,686
Why didn't you wake me up
when you were heading out?

78
00:05:59,687 --> 00:06:01,987
I can't believe
you just left me there.

79
00:06:01,987 --> 00:06:04,051
You were sound asleep.

80
00:06:04,727 --> 00:06:06,857
If it's something to do
with the hospital, I could...

81
00:06:06,857 --> 00:06:09,222
You didn't wake me up
because I was sound asleep?

82
00:06:10,396 --> 00:06:13,892
Does it mean you peeked at me
when I was sleeping?

83
00:06:15,836 --> 00:06:17,466
What are you talking about?

84
00:06:17,466 --> 00:06:20,301
Anyone could see
that you were fast asleep.

85
00:06:21,607 --> 00:06:24,301
Sure, all right.

86
00:06:26,247 --> 00:06:29,481
I have a tutoring session later.
I'll see you at home.

87
00:06:32,047 --> 00:06:36,082
Gosh, that makes it sound like
we live together, doesn't it?

88
00:06:39,156 --> 00:06:40,692
Nonsense.

89
00:06:41,057 --> 00:06:43,692
Get going already.

90
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:49,161
See you later.

91
00:07:00,146 --> 00:07:02,442
(Letter of Resignation)

92
00:07:06,857 --> 00:07:08,351
Oh, dear.

93
00:07:08,756 --> 00:07:11,057
You always talked about going abroad
since you were a newbie.

94
00:07:11,057 --> 00:07:12,822
Are you finally going?

95
00:07:14,297 --> 00:07:16,597
Even if you submit
this resignation letter,

96
00:07:16,597 --> 00:07:18,491
you know you have to work
for another month, right?

97
00:07:18,566 --> 00:07:21,696
I'll work extra hard until I leave,

98
00:07:21,696 --> 00:07:22,962
so don't you worry.

99
00:07:30,276 --> 00:07:31,442
Hello?

100
00:07:31,847 --> 00:07:32,972
Hey, Myeong Hee.

101
00:07:34,076 --> 00:07:36,311
Today? Sure, I have time.

102
00:07:37,386 --> 00:07:38,481
Why?

103
00:07:38,586 --> 00:07:40,551
Did Hwang Hee Tae bother you again?

104
00:07:42,417 --> 00:07:43,882
I'm glad to hear that.

105
00:07:44,386 --> 00:07:45,952
Do you want to come over after work?

106
00:07:53,097 --> 00:07:55,561
Soo Chan, aren't you going to work?

107
00:07:56,037 --> 00:07:58,462
Auntie is coming over today.

108
00:07:58,906 --> 00:08:00,501
Oh, right.

109
00:08:01,406 --> 00:08:04,142
I guess I'll have to meet
Myeong Hee somewhere else.

110
00:08:06,076 --> 00:08:07,741
No need for that.

111
00:08:08,276 --> 00:08:11,041
We have plenty of food at home.
Just tell her to come over.

112
00:08:11,747 --> 00:08:14,251
Gosh, I don't want to hear
Auntie's nagging.

113
00:08:14,987 --> 00:08:16,656
She'll start nagging me now...

114
00:08:16,656 --> 00:08:17,987
since you'll be
getting married soon.

115
00:08:17,987 --> 00:08:19,927
Who says I'm getting married?

116
00:08:19,927 --> 00:08:22,851
Aren't you about to?
I'm sure I'm not.

117
00:08:24,497 --> 00:08:26,861
Why? Did you two fight again?

118
00:08:29,706 --> 00:08:31,706
I told you
that you have the wrong number.

119
00:08:31,706 --> 00:08:33,801
How many times is this already?

120
00:08:37,947 --> 00:08:40,241
Ma'am, who was that?

121
00:08:41,847 --> 00:08:43,217
The thing is,

122
00:08:43,217 --> 00:08:46,082
someone keeps calling
since this morning...

123
00:08:46,146 --> 00:08:48,457
asking if this is
some kind of publishing company.

124
00:08:48,457 --> 00:08:50,322
Wait, I received that call too.

125
00:08:50,587 --> 00:08:52,251
Wasn't it Jihye Publishing?

126
00:08:52,357 --> 00:08:54,792
Oh, you're right.

127
00:08:54,926 --> 00:08:56,662
Oh, that...

128
00:08:59,737 --> 00:09:01,636
- Oh, gosh.
- My goodness, Soo Ryeon.

129
00:09:01,636 --> 00:09:04,562
Soo Chan, I have to go somewhere.

130
00:09:04,607 --> 00:09:06,506
What? I thought Myeong Hee
was coming over.

131
00:09:06,506 --> 00:09:08,501
Oh. If she comes,

132
00:09:08,676 --> 00:09:11,101
tell her to wait in my room.

133
00:09:11,776 --> 00:09:13,072
Wait a minute...

134
00:09:13,546 --> 00:09:15,542
Hey, Soo Ryeon!

135
00:09:25,426 --> 00:09:28,751
Sir, I'm from Jihye Publishing.

136
00:09:39,977 --> 00:09:41,131
Hey.

137
00:09:41,406 --> 00:09:44,241
No one is coming after you,
so you can eat slowly.

138
00:09:45,107 --> 00:09:47,241
Take off your shoes too.

139
00:09:53,386 --> 00:09:55,981
Gosh, I'm so sorry.

140
00:09:56,556 --> 00:09:58,822
I couldn't call anyone,
not even my house.

141
00:10:00,957 --> 00:10:04,361
Has anything been decided in Seoul?

142
00:10:05,926 --> 00:10:08,092
They've decided to hold
a full protest,

143
00:10:08,237 --> 00:10:09,631
and the leaders will get together...

144
00:10:09,666 --> 00:10:12,332
on the ninth at Korea University
to set up a specific plan.

145
00:10:13,406 --> 00:10:15,871
How are things at the university?

146
00:10:17,406 --> 00:10:18,702
Pretty much the same.

147
00:10:19,676 --> 00:10:22,247
We'll shift the focus from
government-funded professors...

148
00:10:22,247 --> 00:10:23,781
to demanding
the withdrawal of martial law.

149
00:10:24,146 --> 00:10:26,082
We're still working closely
with Chosun University...

150
00:10:26,686 --> 00:10:29,457
and trying our best
to fill your shoes,

151
00:10:29,457 --> 00:10:30,722
so don't worry.

152
00:10:32,026 --> 00:10:35,052
Won Seok, are you in there?

153
00:10:35,097 --> 00:10:36,367
You have a call.

154
00:10:36,367 --> 00:10:39,166
He says his name is Sang Min.

155
00:10:39,166 --> 00:10:40,562
Sang Min?

156
00:10:43,036 --> 00:10:44,162
Wait.

157
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:47,731
I never told her my name.

158
00:10:55,877 --> 00:10:58,842
Won Seok,
don't make this worse than it is.

159
00:11:02,217 --> 00:11:04,582
What are you doing? Get out of here!

160
00:11:21,036 --> 00:11:23,141
Why isn't she coming?

161
00:11:23,747 --> 00:11:25,447
(Lee Ji Eun, 22,
Ewha Womans University)

162
00:11:25,447 --> 00:11:27,276
This young lady is
the youngest daughter...

163
00:11:27,276 --> 00:11:28,576
of Baekwoon Textile.

164
00:11:28,577 --> 00:11:32,247
She may be young,
but I hear she's an elegant lady.

165
00:11:32,247 --> 00:11:33,412
- Auntie.
- What?

166
00:11:33,556 --> 00:11:36,452
I'm really not interested
in blind dates.

167
00:11:36,656 --> 00:11:38,851
Why you little...

168
00:11:39,227 --> 00:11:41,727
You'll turn 30 soon!

169
00:11:41,727 --> 00:11:43,827
If you keep living
as a lonely old bachelor,

170
00:11:43,827 --> 00:11:45,462
you'll humiliate our family.

171
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:48,067
You should tie the knot
before Soo Ryeon...

172
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:50,001
so people don't talk
behind our backs.

173
00:11:50,067 --> 00:11:51,962
Goodness, this is driving me crazy.

174
00:11:52,766 --> 00:11:53,932
Hey, Myeong Hee.

175
00:11:54,276 --> 00:11:55,901
Are you leaving already?

176
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:57,172
Yes.

177
00:11:57,806 --> 00:11:59,717
- I'd better get going.
- Hey.

178
00:11:59,717 --> 00:12:01,416
Did you say
you're Soo Ryeon's friend?

179
00:12:01,416 --> 00:12:03,546
Can you come over
and look at this with me?

180
00:12:03,546 --> 00:12:04,987
Look at what?

181
00:12:04,987 --> 00:12:07,552
Women are a better judge of women,
I tell you.

182
00:12:07,656 --> 00:12:10,222
Why don't you come and have a seat?
Come on.

183
00:12:12,127 --> 00:12:13,426
(Choi Eun Ji, 26,
Lee Ji Eun, 22)

184
00:12:13,426 --> 00:12:17,026
Who do you think is
the best candidate?

185
00:12:17,026 --> 00:12:19,367
Number 1 is 26 years old.

186
00:12:19,367 --> 00:12:21,666
She's the eldest daughter
of a judge.

187
00:12:21,666 --> 00:12:22,962
Number two is...

188
00:12:23,467 --> 00:12:26,361
22 years old. The youngest daughter
of Baekwoon Textile.

189
00:12:26,977 --> 00:12:30,072
- Number 3 is 24...
- Auntie!

190
00:12:35,877 --> 00:12:38,981
Who do you think you're yelling at?

191
00:12:39,857 --> 00:12:41,981
Why don't you choose someone
yourself then?

192
00:12:43,056 --> 00:12:46,857
Naive guys like you always let
cunning girls coax you...

193
00:12:46,857 --> 00:12:49,026
and end up bringing home
the worst girls.

194
00:12:49,026 --> 00:12:51,121
Auntie, you'd better go now.

195
00:12:51,867 --> 00:12:53,436
Are you kicking me out right now?

196
00:12:53,436 --> 00:12:55,197
I'll take care of myself,

197
00:12:55,197 --> 00:12:56,506
so please mind your own business.

198
00:12:56,506 --> 00:12:59,536
What? Hey, Soo Chan,
how can you say that to me?

199
00:12:59,536 --> 00:13:01,276
- Please just go.
- What are you doing?

200
00:13:01,276 --> 00:13:04,347
Let go of me. I said, let go!

201
00:13:04,347 --> 00:13:07,176
Am I a stranger to you?
I'm your aunt!

202
00:13:07,176 --> 00:13:09,312
Please! Go!

203
00:13:12,447 --> 00:13:13,781
I'm sorry.

204
00:13:13,987 --> 00:13:16,987
She's a very feisty woman.

205
00:13:16,987 --> 00:13:19,851
She's just doing that
to find you a perfect match.

206
00:13:20,426 --> 00:13:23,092
They all seemed like
great candidates...

207
00:13:26,197 --> 00:13:28,636
I bet your aunt is going through
so much trouble for you...

208
00:13:28,636 --> 00:13:30,261
since you're so picky.

209
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:32,731
What? I'm not picky.

210
00:13:33,577 --> 00:13:34,802
I just don't like blind dates.

211
00:13:36,847 --> 00:13:39,306
It's not like someone can meet
their other half...

212
00:13:39,306 --> 00:13:41,741
based on
some silly matchmaking cards.

213
00:13:44,016 --> 00:13:45,542
I'll look around too.

214
00:13:45,717 --> 00:13:47,552
There are plenty of girls around me.

215
00:13:48,857 --> 00:13:50,281
What's your ideal type?

216
00:14:00,436 --> 00:14:02,162
Someone who's like a wildflower,
I guess?

217
00:14:05,337 --> 00:14:06,977
Someone who never gives up
on her dream...

218
00:14:06,977 --> 00:14:09,072
no matter how hard it is...

219
00:14:10,107 --> 00:14:11,347
and never complains...

220
00:14:11,347 --> 00:14:12,901
about having to devote herself
to her family.

221
00:14:16,377 --> 00:14:20,011
A strong person that says no
to a sheltered life.

222
00:14:29,256 --> 00:14:30,722
That's you.

223
00:14:31,597 --> 00:14:33,067
Aren't I right?

224
00:14:33,067 --> 00:14:35,432
Your ideal type is
a female version of yourself.

225
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:38,832
Gosh, it'll be very hard to find
someone like that.

226
00:14:43,977 --> 00:14:46,101
("It's Been a Long Time,"
Love and Peace)

227
00:14:59,957 --> 00:15:02,722
Then who is
Myeong Hee's favorite singer?

228
00:15:04,127 --> 00:15:05,361
I'm not sure.

229
00:15:06,166 --> 00:15:07,261
Bae In Sook?

230
00:15:07,436 --> 00:15:08,792
Bae In Sook.

231
00:15:09,737 --> 00:15:11,631
Then what is
Myeong Hee's favorite snack?

232
00:15:12,036 --> 00:15:14,972
Sweet red bean jelly
and butter bread?

233
00:15:15,036 --> 00:15:16,942
Sweet red bean jelly
and butter bread?

234
00:15:18,447 --> 00:15:20,871
But what does this have to do
with math?

235
00:15:23,516 --> 00:15:26,617
It's a necessary step
to figure out your study pattern.

236
00:15:26,617 --> 00:15:29,011
Your previous tutor
used to be Myeong Hee, right?

237
00:15:29,156 --> 00:15:30,556
If you don't review your past,

238
00:15:30,556 --> 00:15:32,481
you will never move forward.

239
00:15:35,656 --> 00:15:36,822
Jin A?

240
00:15:37,396 --> 00:15:38,991
I have a new dream.

241
00:15:39,936 --> 00:15:41,891
If I win an award
at the University Song Festival,

242
00:15:42,396 --> 00:15:45,101
I want you to play my song
on the radio show...

243
00:15:45,107 --> 00:15:46,562
that you produce in the future.

244
00:15:47,077 --> 00:15:49,371
And the DJ will say,

245
00:15:49,636 --> 00:15:50,947
"This is the musician..."

246
00:15:50,947 --> 00:15:53,572
"that our producer discovered
before anyone else in the world."

247
00:15:53,817 --> 00:15:55,312
- Hee Tae.
- What do you think?

248
00:15:55,877 --> 00:15:57,582
Will you help me achieve my dream?

249
00:16:00,886 --> 00:16:04,381
Then will you help me
achieve my dream?

250
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:08,452
Can you show me around Seoul
this summer break?

251
00:16:08,457 --> 00:16:11,462
Show me TBC's broadcasting station
and your university too!

252
00:16:19,906 --> 00:16:21,806
If you promise you'll do
all the homework I give you.

253
00:16:21,806 --> 00:16:23,401
- I promise.
- Okay.

254
00:16:23,506 --> 00:16:25,141
From here...

255
00:16:25,906 --> 00:16:27,072
to here.

256
00:16:29,516 --> 00:16:31,987
You want me to solve
all these questions?

257
00:16:31,987 --> 00:16:33,617
Yes. If you start now,

258
00:16:33,617 --> 00:16:35,552
you'll probably be done
in about two days.

