Hey, wait!

522
00:36:51,986 --> 00:36:54,681
Hey, can you please not do this
during exam season?

523
00:36:55,086 --> 00:36:57,427
Just take him to the hospital.

524
00:36:57,427 --> 00:37:00,022
You know I brought him here
because I can't do that.

525
00:37:14,677 --> 00:37:15,871
Please be gentle.

526
00:37:18,617 --> 00:37:20,077
You won't find a surgeon...

527
00:37:20,077 --> 00:37:23,181
who'd be gentler than this
even at a university hospital.

528
00:37:23,486 --> 00:37:24,641
That's true.

529
00:37:24,716 --> 00:37:27,081
He's the top student
at our med school.

530
00:37:27,387 --> 00:37:29,026
- We call him Hua Tuo.
- Hua Tuo, my foot.

531
00:37:29,026 --> 00:37:31,422
I'll stitch your lips together.

532
00:37:31,586 --> 00:37:32,696
Hua Tuo?

533
00:37:32,696 --> 00:37:34,152
Is my specialty treating fugitives?

534
00:37:35,796 --> 00:37:38,291
What if I get caught doing this
and get expelled from school?

535
00:37:38,497 --> 00:37:40,061
Will you take responsibility
for my future?

536
00:37:40,966 --> 00:37:42,232
Yes, I should.

537
00:37:42,566 --> 00:37:44,632
I'll write lyrics
while you compose songs.

538
00:37:45,376 --> 00:37:47,106
We'll win the grand prize
at the University Song Festival.

539
00:37:47,106 --> 00:37:49,247
You troublemaker.

540
00:37:49,247 --> 00:37:52,311
At this rate,
we'll be dragged to Namsan first.

541
00:37:55,387 --> 00:37:56,511
Seriously!

542
00:37:56,617 --> 00:37:58,541
Stay still
while I'm stitching the wound.

543
00:37:59,617 --> 00:38:01,782
- Careful. Watch your step.
- Thanks.

544
00:38:06,497 --> 00:38:07,652
Hee Tae,

545
00:38:08,057 --> 00:38:09,991
you'll be a great doctor.

546
00:38:11,267 --> 00:38:13,466
Go write some lyrics
for the song festival.

547
00:38:13,466 --> 00:38:15,502
Don't use the night school
as an excuse to date.

548
00:38:15,637 --> 00:38:17,962
Hey, what are you talking about?

549
00:38:18,307 --> 00:38:19,537
You know what I'm talking about.

550
00:38:19,537 --> 00:38:21,871
I can tell from the lyrics
you've been writing!

551
00:38:27,146 --> 00:38:28,272
Hey.

552
00:38:29,387 --> 00:38:31,842
Don't bring anyone else, please.

553
00:38:32,657 --> 00:38:33,811
Thanks.

554
00:38:34,457 --> 00:38:35,827
- Get going.
- Bye.

555
00:38:35,827 --> 00:38:36,951
Bye.

556
00:38:56,946 --> 00:38:58,641
Hey, do you realize what time it is?

557
00:39:00,247 --> 00:39:01,442
Hee Tae.

558
00:39:02,446 --> 00:39:04,041
Please save Seok Chul.

559
00:39:17,896 --> 00:39:19,092
Her pulse is weak,

560
00:39:19,796 --> 00:39:21,061
and she's lost a lot of blood.

561
00:39:21,437 --> 00:39:22,802
You should take her to the hospital.

562
00:39:23,407 --> 00:39:25,376
No, not the hospital.

563
00:39:25,376 --> 00:39:28,532
I know you brought her to me
because you can't take her there.

564
00:39:28,577 --> 00:39:29,672
Darn it.

565
00:39:32,646 --> 00:39:34,141
You know the small clinic
down the street?

566
00:39:34,347 --> 00:39:35,916
Knock on the door,
and someone will come out.

567
00:39:35,916 --> 00:39:37,316
Tell them I sent you.
It's my friend's clinic.

568
00:39:37,316 --> 00:39:38,482
Okay.

569
00:39:47,057 --> 00:39:48,152
Hee Tae.

570
00:39:49,827 --> 00:39:50,922
Save her.

571
00:39:51,566 --> 00:39:53,632
You must save her, no matter what.

572
00:39:53,966 --> 00:39:55,962
Okay. You need to hurry.

573
00:40:07,946 --> 00:40:09,241
Darn it.

574
00:40:12,557 --> 00:40:14,652
Gosh, this is crazy.

575
00:40:30,637 --> 00:40:31,761
Stop!

576
00:40:33,477 --> 00:40:35,902
- Let go! Let go of me!
- Stay still!

577
00:40:36,276 --> 00:40:37,677
- Let go of me.
- Hey!

578
00:40:37,677 --> 00:40:38,942
Cuff this punk.

579
00:40:42,986 --> 00:40:44,081
Please...

580
00:40:45,247 --> 00:40:47,681
Can someone please come
and help me? Anyone?

581
00:41:05,437 --> 00:41:06,632
Hee Tae.

582
00:41:10,046 --> 00:41:11,201
Hee Tae.

583
00:41:39,006 --> 00:41:40,732
I'm not qualified to be a doctor.

584
00:41:44,977 --> 00:41:47,471
I chose this path
because I wanted to treat the ill,

585
00:41:50,517 --> 00:41:51,712
but everything I touch...

586
00:41:52,557 --> 00:41:54,052
just breaks.

587
00:42:05,227 --> 00:42:07,391
Maybe your heart is the one
that is broken.

588
00:42:11,336 --> 00:42:12,772
You know,

589
00:42:13,137 --> 00:42:15,802
we don't decide who lives or dies.

590
00:42:16,807 --> 00:42:18,672
That decision is up to the Almighty.

591
00:42:20,177 --> 00:42:23,011
All we can do is do our best
within the lines...

592
00:42:25,117 --> 00:42:26,911
drawn by the Almighty.

593
00:42:31,557 --> 00:42:32,951
And...

594
00:42:33,327 --> 00:42:35,862
if I may share my opinion
as someone...

595
00:42:36,696 --> 00:42:38,522
who's working in the same field,

596
00:42:40,637 --> 00:42:41,791
I know for a fact...

597
00:42:44,537 --> 00:42:46,632
that you'll be a great doctor.

598
00:42:48,276 --> 00:42:49,977
You're beating yourself up
like this...

599
00:42:49,977 --> 00:42:51,802
because you're
a very responsible person.

600
00:42:53,816 --> 00:42:55,511
And people like that
are hard to come by.

601
00:43:03,657 --> 00:43:05,152
I'm not being sarcastic.

602
00:43:31,687 --> 00:43:32,811
There.

603
00:44:13,296 --> 00:44:15,791
I can't believe you did this again
knowing what's going on.

604
00:44:15,966 --> 00:44:18,022
Aren't you ashamed
to face your family?

605
00:44:18,666 --> 00:44:20,696
I've never done anything
to be ashamed of.

606
00:44:20,696 --> 00:44:21,937
How could you say that...

607
00:44:21,937 --> 00:44:24,201
after humiliating me in front of
your future father-in-law?

608
00:44:24,466 --> 00:44:25,632
Father.

609
00:44:28,137 --> 00:44:30,641
I won't get married.

610
00:44:30,677 --> 00:44:32,477
What? What are you talking about?

611
00:44:32,477 --> 00:44:33,641
I just...

612
00:44:33,946 --> 00:44:36,112
couldn't muster up the courage
to say this to you.

613
00:44:37,216 --> 00:44:39,086
I have no interest
in getting married...

614
00:44:39,086 --> 00:44:40,756
and getting involved
with that kind of family...

615
00:44:40,756 --> 00:44:43,552
That family will help us
with the business.

616
00:44:43,887 --> 00:44:45,022
What?

617
00:44:45,157 --> 00:44:46,427
The company is about to go bust,

618
00:44:46,427 --> 00:44:48,626
so I couldn't turn down their offer.

619
00:44:48,626 --> 00:44:50,592
All my enemies want my business
to go bust.

620
00:44:51,296 --> 00:44:52,867
And my daughter jumps into flames...

621
00:44:52,867 --> 00:44:54,166
with gunpowder in her hand
any chance she gets.

622
00:44:54,166 --> 00:44:56,561
So what choice do I have?

623
00:44:56,807 --> 00:44:58,207
Father!

624
00:44:58,207 --> 00:44:59,471
It's already decided.

625
00:44:59,677 --> 00:45:00,772
Earlier today,

626
00:45:01,037 --> 00:45:03,442
your brother met the investor
they put us in touch with.

627
00:45:04,577 --> 00:45:05,646
Technical partnerships...

628
00:45:05,646 --> 00:45:08,241
are already very common
in other countries.

629
00:45:08,446 --> 00:45:11,782
The construction for the factory
is expected to be completed soon.

630
00:45:11,847 --> 00:45:13,252
So I'm certain...

631
00:45:13,356 --> 00:45:15,482
we can start selling the products
by the end of this year.

632
00:45:15,827 --> 00:45:18,026
(Lee Soo Chan,
Changhwa Pharmaceuticals)

633
00:45:18,026 --> 00:45:20,026
This isn't some kids' game.
We can't just back out...

634
00:45:20,026 --> 00:45:21,891
because we've now changed our minds.

635
00:45:22,227 --> 00:45:23,896
With just one word,
he can make companies go bankrupt...

636
00:45:23,896 --> 00:45:25,192
and make people disappear.

637
00:45:25,427 --> 00:45:26,566
You, of all people,

638
00:45:26,566 --> 00:45:28,561
must know
what Mr. Hwang is capable of.

639
00:45:30,367 --> 00:45:31,502
Just get married.

640
00:45:32,336 --> 00:45:34,532
I don't care if people criticize me
for selling off my daughter.

641
00:45:34,776 --> 00:45:36,041
Our family...

642
00:45:36,506 --> 00:45:39,442
is already on the back of the tiger.
If we fall off,

643
00:45:41,276 --> 00:45:42,741
we'll get eaten alive.

644
00:45:51,726 --> 00:45:56,726
<font color="#0080ff">[Kocowa Ver] KBS E08 'Youth of May'</font>
<font color="#ff8080">"Hee Tae's Trauma"</font>
<font color="#ff0080">-♥ Ruo Xi ♥-</font>
<font color="#0080ff">Synced with Subcake Android</font>

645
00:46:06,876 --> 00:46:09,402
- What...
- I can go on my own from here.

646
00:46:09,477 --> 00:46:12,276
Why? Let me go with you.
We're almost there anyway.

647
00:46:12,276 --> 00:46:14,311
That's why I can go alone.

648
00:46:14,477 --> 00:46:17,112
Jin A might cause a fuss
if she sees us.

649
00:46:17,316 --> 00:46:20,517
Come on, she's probably busy
doing her homework right now.

650
00:46:20,517 --> 00:46:22,152
I can go alone.

651
00:46:24,687 --> 00:46:26,121
Okay then.

652
00:46:26,756 --> 00:46:29,092
I enjoyed today's picnic,
Myeong Hee.

653
00:46:29,466 --> 00:46:30,721
Handshake?

654
00:46:38,707 --> 00:46:42,132
Me too.
Thank you for everything today.

655
00:46:55,086 --> 00:46:58,621
Look back.

656
00:46:59,696 --> 00:47:03,661
Look back. Look back...

657
00:47:04,367 --> 00:47:05,931
Look back!

658
00:47:15,707 --> 00:47:18,471
Hey! Gosh.

659
00:47:18,707 --> 00:47:22,011
I was wishing you'd look back.

660
00:47:22,017 --> 00:47:23,382
Did you hear it?

661
00:47:26,356 --> 00:47:27,851
I'll give you my answer...

662
00:47:28,756 --> 00:47:30,252
tomorrow.

663
00:47:36,966 --> 00:47:39,232
Can't you answer me today?

664
00:47:40,336 --> 00:47:42,661
There's something
I need to sort out.

665
00:47:43,466 --> 00:47:46,032
I'll tell you tomorrow afternoon
after my shift.

666
00:47:46,907 --> 00:47:48,132
Here.

667
00:48:04,687 --> 00:48:06,422
Yes!

668
00:48:14,396 --> 00:48:16,701
(Head of Anti-communist
Investigation, Hwang Ki Nam)

669
00:48:45,066 --> 00:48:48,491
(Kim Myeong Hee)

670
00:48:48,966 --> 00:48:51,931
(Father, Kim Hyun Chul)

671
00:48:56,946 --> 00:49:00,112
(Kim Hyun Chul, Choi Soon Nyu,
Kim Myeong Soo)

672
00:49:23,907 --> 00:49:26,376
- Hello?
- Hey, Soo Ryeon.

673
00:49:26,376 --> 00:49:29,741
What happened the other day?
I couldn't reach you.

674
00:49:31,407 --> 00:49:35,471
Myeong Hee.
Something suddenly came up.

675
00:49:36,416 --> 00:49:39,612
What? Is it something serious?

676
00:49:40,216 --> 00:49:42,882
No. It's not serious at all.

677
00:49:43,086 --> 00:49:45,252
So, what's up?

678
00:49:46,327 --> 00:49:50,661
Can I see you
before I go to work later?

679
00:49:50,966 --> 00:49:54,862
The thing is...
I have something to tell you.

680
00:50:00,937 --> 00:50:04,601
Sorry, I don't have time today.

681
00:50:05,847 --> 00:50:08,241
I have plans.

682
00:50:09,146 --> 00:50:11,342
(Watch repair)

683
00:50:17,086 --> 00:50:18,887
Can I get my watch repaired now?

684
00:50:18,887 --> 00:50:22,522
You'll have to wait
about 15 minutes.

685
00:50:23,026 --> 00:50:24,991
Can't you look at mine first?

686
00:50:24,997 --> 00:50:26,831
I just need a new battery.

687
00:50:26,867 --> 00:50:28,391
Let me see it.

688
00:50:34,836 --> 00:50:38,041
(The Blue House)

689
00:50:44,517 --> 00:50:47,081
Oh, look who it is.

690
00:50:47,287 --> 00:50:49,212
Aren't you Hyun Chul?

691
00:50:50,187 --> 00:50:52,621
How have you been?

692
00:50:53,126 --> 00:50:55,221
Is your mother still alive?

693
00:51:02,497 --> 00:51:04,232
Just tell me what you want.

694
00:51:05,106 --> 00:51:07,572
There's no need to be so edgy.

695
00:51:07,677 --> 00:51:09,776
I just came to get a new battery
and see you as well.

696
00:51:09,776 --> 00:51:11,302
We're old neighborhood friends
after all.

697
00:51:16,586 --> 00:51:20,052
I see your daughter is having
a lot of fun lately.

698
00:51:21,187 --> 00:51:23,322
Keep a good eye on your daughter.

699
00:51:23,356 --> 00:51:25,221
She's not a kid anymore.

700
00:51:25,586 --> 00:51:27,491
I won't go easy either.

701
00:51:39,836 --> 00:51:41,371
You don't have to pay me.

702
00:51:47,776 --> 00:51:49,342
I'll see you later.

703
00:52:00,126 --> 00:52:01,896
Let me say it again.

704
00:52:01,896 --> 00:52:05,721
The most important thing
in track and field is the line.

705
00:52:07,336 --> 00:52:09,097
Especially when you run,

706
00:52:09,097 --> 00:52:12,735
if you cross into
another runner's track,

707
00:52:12,736 --> 00:52:16,471
you may get disqualified
for deviating from your own track.

708
00:52:16,977 --> 00:52:20,347
Hence, do not trespass
into another runner's zone,

709
00:52:20,347 --> 00:52:23,046
and always stay within your line...

710
00:52:23,046 --> 00:52:24,887
and run as fast as you can.

711
00:52:24,887 --> 00:52:27,681
That's my main point.

712
00:52:29,586 --> 00:52:31,157
- Can I help you?
- Oh, yes.

713
00:52:31,157 --> 00:52:34,022
Is there a boy named
Myeong Soo here?

714
00:52:34,196 --> 00:52:35,692
That's me.

715
00:52:37,727 --> 00:52:39,221
Father.

716
00:52:40,137 --> 00:52:42,561
Be careful, you might fall down.

717
00:52:42,597 --> 00:52:45,462
Why are you here?
I thought you were coming tomorrow.

718
00:52:45,836 --> 00:52:47,201
No reason.

719
00:52:47,207 --> 00:52:50,402
I missed my little bear,
so I came early.

720
00:52:51,907 --> 00:52:53,876
How is Myeong Hee doing?

721
00:52:53,876 --> 00:52:55,376
She's doing fine.

722
00:52:55,376 --> 00:52:58,187
Father, I shortened my record
by two seconds.

723
00:52:58,187 --> 00:52:59,687
My coach told me...

724
00:52:59,687 --> 00:53:02,256
that I can run
with the middle schooler next time.

725
00:53:02,256 --> 00:53:03,727
Is that so?

726
00:53:03,727 --> 00:53:06,152
Gosh, that's amazing, son.

727
00:53:06,457 --> 00:53:09,296
Are you getting along well
with the other kids?

728
00:53:09,296 --> 00:53:12,592
Well, almost all of them,
except for one guy.

729
00:53:16,707 --> 00:53:19,971
Hey. Are you Myeong Soo's friend?

730
00:53:23,446 --> 00:53:25,302
Speak of the devil.

731
00:53:26,177 --> 00:53:28,741
Man, that annoying jerk.

732
00:53:29,517 --> 00:53:31,141
Don't say that to a friend.

733
00:53:35,486 --> 00:53:36,586
Here.

734
00:53:36,586 --> 00:53:39,652
I bought plenty,
so share it with the others.

735
00:53:39,957 --> 00:53:42,057
Wait, isn't this pulbbang?

736
00:53:42,057 --> 00:53:44,761
Gosh, you didn't have to.

737
00:53:45,097 --> 00:53:48,836
My goodness.
Where did you learn to say that?

738
00:53:48,836 --> 00:53:51,002
You don't have to say that to me.

739
00:53:54,577 --> 00:53:55,732
Me too?

740
00:53:58,106 --> 00:53:59,971
It's good.

741
00:54:00,177 --> 00:54:02,416
Hey, let's go this way.

742
00:54:02,416 --> 00:54:03,916
I told you!

743
00:54:03,916 --> 00:54:06,687
I told you it's this way.

744
00:54:06,687 --> 00:54:08,887
Come on, let's go.

745
00:54:08,887 --> 00:54:11,581
- Hurry up, it's this way.
- Okay.

746
00:54:18,597 --> 00:54:21,831
I'd better get going now.

747
00:54:22,166 --> 00:54:23,437
Already?

748
00:54:23,437 --> 00:54:25,137
You should come meet my coach...

749
00:54:25,137 --> 00:54:27,502
and the place I'm staying at.

750
00:54:28,637 --> 00:54:30,842
It's okay, there's no need.

751
00:54:31,506 --> 00:54:34,911
Your mom sent
some clothes and underwear.

752
00:54:35,316 --> 00:54:38,411
You should go now. Go on.

753
00:54:42,086 --> 00:54:43,382
Go on.

754
00:54:43,887 --> 00:54:46,052
Go on now.

755
00:55:07,876 --> 00:55:09,842
Hey, isn't that pulbbang?

756
00:55:11,146 --> 00:55:14,451
Let's go inside and eat it
before the others see us.

757
00:55:15,287 --> 00:55:17,851
Shall I call Jung Tae over?

758
00:55:23,367 --> 00:55:25,462
Let's just keep it a secret.

759
00:55:39,407 --> 00:55:42,371
Do it again! That's so funny.

760
00:56:19,486 --> 00:56:21,287
I don't have time
for bickering today.

761
00:56:21,287 --> 00:56:23,052
Get straight to the point.

762
00:56:26,187 --> 00:56:28,451
I met your father yesterday
at the Defense Security Command.

763
00:56:29,867 --> 00:56:31,121
He tried to threaten me...

764
00:56:31,896 --> 00:56:33,331
into getting engaged to you.

765
00:56:35,597 --> 00:56:37,002
That's my father's specialty.

766
00:56:37,537 --> 00:56:38,632
So?

767
00:56:41,537 --> 00:56:44,201
Your family is getting involved
in my father's business.

768
00:56:45,006 --> 00:56:46,471
Did you know that?

769
00:56:52,086 --> 00:56:53,351
How would I have known?

770
00:56:56,086 --> 00:56:57,282
Like I said,

771
00:56:58,026 --> 00:57:00,522
we won't be able to back out
once things get more serious.

772
00:57:03,566 --> 00:57:05,192
So what's your plan?

773
00:57:08,637 --> 00:57:10,161
My father's factory...

774
00:57:11,336 --> 00:57:13,002
will be finished in a month.

775
00:57:16,747 --> 00:57:19,871
Let's keep this up until then.

776
00:57:21,017 --> 00:57:23,041
After that, I'll do as you say.

777
00:57:27,557 --> 00:57:28,752
Once the factory is finished,

778
00:57:28,986 --> 00:57:31,626
should we get engaged to make sure
the factory runs smoothly...

779
00:57:31,626 --> 00:57:33,057
and even get married...

780
00:57:33,057 --> 00:57:34,727
until the business takes off?

781
00:57:34,727 --> 00:57:36,322
I don't need your sarcasm.

782
00:57:36,427 --> 00:57:38,422
This is driving me crazy as it is.

783
00:57:38,466 --> 00:57:40,497
Fine. I'll be straightforward then.

784
00:57:40,497 --> 00:57:41,661
I don't want to.

785
00:57:43,267 --> 00:57:45,232
- You don't want to?
- No.

786
00:57:48,577 --> 00:57:50,002
Then what about
my father's business?

787
00:57:50,506 --> 00:57:51,907
What about my family?

788
00:57:51,907 --> 00:57:55,077
Look, don't put all the blame on me.

789
00:57:55,077 --> 00:57:56,387
You started all this.

790
00:57:56,387 --> 00:57:57,612
Hwang Hee Tae.

791
00:58:16,137 --> 00:58:17,661
Let's tell the truth...

792
00:58:18,137 --> 00:58:19,502
and take responsibility equally.

793
00:58:19,977 --> 00:58:23,172
We shouldn't cross the line
just to save ourselves for now.

794
00:58:30,916 --> 00:58:32,911
If you need someone
to beg for forgiveness with you,

795
00:58:33,957 --> 00:58:35,081
call me.

796
00:58:58,707 --> 00:58:59,971
Why did you do that?

797
00:59:03,046 --> 00:59:04,212
I mean earlier.

798
00:59:04,946 --> 00:59:06,442
Why did you punch him?

799
00:59:08,517 --> 00:59:10,951
Just because. I couldn't stand him.

800
00:59:11,727 --> 00:59:13,991
You're impossible.

801
00:59:14,657 --> 00:59:16,822
Didn't you hear
what the coach said earlier?

802
00:59:17,196 --> 00:59:19,161
"Don't cross the line."

803
00:59:19,997 --> 00:59:22,831
Why cross the line
and get yourself into a mess?

804
00:59:27,707 --> 00:59:30,201
You must've missed
some of the stuff the coach said.

805
00:59:31,106 --> 00:59:32,201
What?

806
00:59:32,376 --> 00:59:35,172
In long-distance running,
it's okay to cross the line.

807
00:59:35,816 --> 00:59:37,347
You need to know
just when to cross the line.

808
00:59:37,347 --> 00:59:38,712
That's what makes a good runner.

809
00:59:40,687 --> 00:59:42,482
And we run 1,000m.

810
00:59:51,597 --> 00:59:53,561
Eat them
before you brush your teeth.

811
01:00:15,787 --> 01:00:16,922
(Cashier)

812
01:00:19,756 --> 01:00:21,856
So Ms. Jang will be transferred
in a private ambulance...

813
01:00:21,856 --> 01:00:23,267
that you hired in Seoul?

814
01:00:23,267 --> 01:00:24,661
Yes.

815
01:00:24,997 --> 01:00:26,732
I already paid for it.

816
01:00:31,966 --> 01:00:34,437
Then please make sure
she is transferred here on time.

817
01:00:34,437 --> 01:00:35,632
(Receipt)

818
01:00:39,106 --> 01:00:41,177
Is everything all set?

819
01:00:41,177 --> 01:00:42,842
Yes, you're good to go.

820
01:00:45,117 --> 01:00:47,851
(Receipt)

821
01:00:49,927 --> 01:00:51,081
Hey, grunt.

822
01:00:51,157 --> 01:00:53,451
It's me again, Hee Tae.

823
01:00:54,457 --> 01:00:57,761
Your dear Seok Chul
will be transferred to Gwangju soon.

824
01:00:58,227 --> 01:01:00,661
So visit her in Gwangju
if you miss her.

825
01:01:06,437 --> 01:01:07,532
You see,

826
01:01:07,907 --> 01:01:09,946
if only you knew
how much trouble I went to,

827
01:01:09,946 --> 01:01:11,871
you'd write me back immediately.

828
01:01:15,376 --> 01:01:18,942
Her transfer won't get you out
of the military...

829
01:01:19,247 --> 01:01:22,112
or help her recover,

830
01:01:23,017 --> 01:01:24,882
but I hope it'll help us all...

831
01:01:25,057 --> 01:01:27,152
finally take a step forward
from that day.

832
01:01:28,057 --> 01:01:30,192
(From Hwang Hee Tae,
To Kim Kyung Soo)

833
01:01:31,566 --> 01:01:33,831
I'm finally ready
to slowly walk forward...

834
01:01:34,396 --> 01:01:36,391
from the line I drew that day.

835
01:01:40,376 --> 01:01:41,876
(Samyang Flower Shop)

836
01:01:41,876 --> 01:01:43,032
PS,

837
01:01:43,577 --> 01:01:45,201
you once told me...

838
01:01:46,177 --> 01:01:49,541
that I wrote bad lyrics
because I didn't know love.

839
01:01:50,816 --> 01:01:52,581
But I think I'm ready now.

840
01:01:53,486 --> 01:01:55,011
There's someone who can help me.

841
01:02:20,446 --> 01:02:21,612
Myeong Hee.

842
01:02:29,856 --> 01:02:31,022
Hee Tae.

843
01:02:32,557 --> 01:02:33,721
Yes?

844
01:02:38,026 --> 01:02:39,322
Can you...

845
01:02:45,207 --> 01:02:46,831
get engaged to Soo Ryeon?

846
01:03:08,557 --> 01:03:11,362
(Youth of May)

847
01:03:24,646 --> 01:03:25,807
To settle the situation,

848
01:03:25,807 --> 01:03:27,747
I thought I should tell you
as soon as possible.

849
01:03:27,747 --> 01:03:28,776
Hwang Hee Tae.

850
01:03:28,776 --> 01:03:31,416
- Aren't we even saying hi now?
- I didn't have time to.

851
01:03:31,416 --> 01:03:33,887
You can continue to see other women
even after you get married.

852
01:03:33,887 --> 01:03:35,057
Like how you dated my mother?

853
01:03:35,057 --> 01:03:37,157
Hwang Ki Nam, the Head of
Anti-communist Investigation, right?

854
01:03:37,157 --> 01:03:39,557
She was picking out a ring,
looking all happy.

855
01:03:39,557 --> 01:03:41,256
I was going to return your favor.

856
01:03:41,256 --> 01:03:44,126
You're supposed to buy a new outfit
when your sibling gets engaged.

857
01:03:44,126 --> 01:03:45,927
- Soo Chan, you're here.
- My future brother-in-law.

858
01:03:45,927 --> 01:03:47,997
My goodness,
you look like a movie star.

859
01:03:47,997 --> 01:03:50,701
Myeong Hee, what are you doing here?

